&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I am currently on the academic job market!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am a final year PhD student in electrical and computer engineering at &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.cmu.edu/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Carnegie Mellon University&lt;/a&gt;, where I am fortunate to have &lt;a href=&#34;http://elaineshi.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Elaine Shi&lt;/a&gt; as my advisor.
My research lies in the intersection between mechanism design and cryptography.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Previously, I was a research assistant at &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.iis.sinica.edu.tw/index_en.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Academia Sinica&lt;/a&gt;, hosted by &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.iis.sinica.edu.tw/~kmchung/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Kai-Min Chung&lt;/a&gt;. Before that, I was a blockchain researcher at DEXON foundation. I got my master&amp;rsquo;s degree in electrical engineering from National Taiwan University, and I got my bachelor&amp;rsquo;s degree from &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ntu.edu.tw/english/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;National Taiwan University&lt;/a&gt;, where I majored in physics and minored in philosophy.&lt;/p&gt;

